comments.body:
Thanks for bringing up the uid. Yes, I agree it is part of the uid.

Regarding the sort order of the user-provided prefix value, my point was really about the user convenience. I do agree for the most part users/frameworks will want to use the most-recent-first order. It's just that it would be slightly better if they can do this more easily. For example, let's say the user wants to use the (inverse) of the "task id". Then they would do

{code}
long taskId = getTaskId();
entity.setIdPrefix(Long.MAX_VALUE - taskId);
{code}

It might be slightly more user-friendly if they did
{code}
long taskId = getTaskId();
entity.setIdPrefix(Util.invertLong(taskId));
{code}

Again, I admit this might be a pretty small point...

